This is the largest centipede in Asia. A consistent character that is treated as diagnostic for this species is the absence of ventral spines on the ultimate leg prefemur. Scolopendra dehaani possesses characters of the Scolopendra subspinipes s.l. sensu Lewis (2010) but after morphological survey (
Kronmueller 2012
) and molecular delimitation ( Siriwut et al. 2015b ) a species rank has been conferred to this name. The morphological variability in the extent of paramedian sutures recorded in some specimens might demand further examination. Three morphotypes of Scolopendra dehaani within the examined collections can de delimited as follow:
